{"article_id":"FYmISHKx8KE86VGo","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Washington ( CNN )","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"President Barack Obama nominated Judge Merrick Garland ,","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"who is respected across political lines ,","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"to the Supreme Court Wednesday , in an epic power play","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"targeting the resolve of Republicans","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"who have vowed to block any replacement for the late Justice Antonin Scalia","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"until a new president takes office .","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"GOP leaders ,","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"caught in the undertow of an election","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"in which the conservative grass-roots are already in revolt ,","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"immediately renewed their refusal","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"to consider Garland , 63 ,","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"saying","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"their reservations were not personal","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"but motivated by a desire","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"for the American people to weigh in on Scalia 's replacement .","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"The showdown is even more fraught than most Supreme Court fights ,","depth":6},{"id":17,"text":"since Obama 's choice could tilt the ideological balance of the court away from conservatives","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"-- possibly for years .","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"In a speech in the evocative ceremonial surroundings of the White House Rose Garden , Obama praised Garland as `` one of America 's sharpest legal minds ,","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"'' making a case","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"that he was so eminently qualified for the job in terms of legal learning , experience and temperament","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"that any attempt","depth":12},{"id":23,"text":"to ignore his appointment","depth":12},{"id":24,"text":"could only be the result of base political motivations .","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"`` I have selected a nominee","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"who is widely recognized not only as one of America 's sharpest legal minds , but someone","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"who brings to his work a spirit of decency modesty , integrity , evenhandedness and excellence , ''","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"Obama said .","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"These qualities and his long commitment to public service have earned him the respect and admiration from leaders from both sides of the aisle . ''","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"Senate Republicans do not plan to vet or have hearings on Garland , let alone a vote on his nomination .","depth":7},{"id":31,"text":"Obama and Democrats argue","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"that with 10 months left in his term , there is plenty of time","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"for the Senate to take up and confirm a new justice .","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"The gravity of Obama 's announcement on Wednesday was part of an attempt","depth":6},{"id":35,"text":"to pressure Republicans ,","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"especially senators with an eye on their own legacies or those","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"who face tough re-election fights ,","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"to peel away from their leadership .","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"Mitch McConnell responds to Supreme Court nomination","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"Mitch McConnell responds to Supreme Court nomination","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"01:16","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"But Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell and the GOP chairman of the Senate Judiciary Committee , Chuck Grassley of Iowa , have both expressed little leeway in their determination","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"to forgo hearings for Obama 's nominee .","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"`` The American people may well elect a president","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"who decides to nominate Judge Garland for Senate consideration , ''","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"McConnell said Wednesday .","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"`` The next president may also nominate someone very different .","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"Either way , our view is this :","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"Give the people a voice in the filling of this vacancy . '' `` Rather than put Judge Garland through more unnecessary political routines","depth":13},{"id":53,"text":"orchestrated by the White House ,","depth":13},{"id":54,"text":"the leader decided","depth":13},{"id":55,"text":"it would be more considerate of the nominee 's time to speak with him today by phone , ''","depth":13},{"id":56,"text":"McConnell spokesman Don Stewart said .","depth":11},{"id":57,"text":"`` And","depth":12},{"id":58,"text":"since the Senate will not be acting on this nomination ,","depth":13},{"id":59,"text":"he would not be holding a perfunctory meeting ,","depth":13},{"id":60,"text":"but he wished Judge Garland well . ''","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"Garland , the chief judge for the U.S. Court of Appeals for the District of Columbia Circuit , has been on short lists before .","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"An appointee of President Bill Clinton , Garland is a graduate of Harvard and Harvard Law School .","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"As a Justice Department lawyer , he supervised investigations in the Unabomber case as well as the Oklahoma City bombing .","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"His voice cracking with emotion ,","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"Garland called Obama 's decision","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"to nominate him","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"`` the greatest honor of my life . ''","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"`` For me , their could be no higher public service","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"than serving as a member of the Supreme Court , ''","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"Garland said .","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"Obama 's announcement amplifies the ongoing political battle over the precedent and propriety","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"of considering a Supreme Court nomination amid a heated presidential election .","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"The announcement comes after a big night in the 2016 election ,","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"with both party 's front-runners","depth":12},{"id":75,"text":"-- Democrat Hillary Clinton and Republican Donald Trump --","depth":12},{"id":76,"text":"emerging with sweeping victories","depth":11},{"id":77,"text":"as they march toward their respective nominations .","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"Some believed","depth":11},{"id":79,"text":"Obama would time his pick","depth":12},{"id":80,"text":"so it would n't get lost in a news cycle","depth":13},{"id":81,"text":"dominated by election results .","depth":13},{"id":82,"text":"But the timing seems suited to directly insert the selection into the political conversation .","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"Fueling the argument is the potential for the first shift in the court 's ideological leaning in two decades .","depth":11},{"id":84,"text":"If confirmed ,","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"Obama 's nominee will likely offer a vastly different legal outlook that Scalia ,","depth":11},{"id":86,"text":"who was considered one of the court 's most conservative members .","depth":11},{"id":87,"text":"CNN senior legal analyst Jeffrey Toobin said","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"the pick of Garland ,","depth":14},{"id":89,"text":"who is well-respected in legal circles","depth":14},{"id":90,"text":"`` takes the issue of qualifications off the table , '' but noted","depth":13},{"id":91,"text":"the fight now is all about politics . ''","depth":12},{"id":92,"text":"`` He is the chief judge of the second most important court in the country ,","depth":14},{"id":93,"text":"but the political calculation here is ,","depth":15},{"id":94,"text":"I think ,","depth":16},{"id":95,"text":"quite clear , ''","depth":16},{"id":96,"text":"Toobin said .","depth":13},{"id":97,"text":"`` President Obama is saying to the Senate Republicans ,","depth":14},{"id":98,"text":"you can take my 63-year-old now","depth":15},{"id":99,"text":"or wait for President Hillary Clinton to bring up a 45-year-old in 10 months . ''","depth":15},{"id":100,"text":"At 63 , Garland is much older than the other contenders on the short list such as Judges Sri Srinivasan , Paul Watford and Jane Kelly .","depth":13},{"id":101,"text":"Garland 's supporters argue","depth":10},{"id":102,"text":"he is the nominee","depth":11},{"id":103,"text":"that the senators could n't refuse even in a contentious environment .","depth":11},{"id":104,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":7},{"id":105,"text":"Obama :","depth":8},{"id":106,"text":"I 'm looking for a 'consensus ' SCOTUS candidate","depth":8},{"id":107,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":7},{"id":108,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":11},{"id":109,"text":"Obama :","depth":12},{"id":110,"text":"I 'm looking for a 'consensus ' SCOTUS candidate","depth":12},{"id":111,"text":"00:40","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"`` It is my intention to nominate somebody","depth":11},{"id":113,"text":"who has impeccable credentials , somebody","depth":12},{"id":114,"text":"who should be a consensus candidate , ''","depth":12},{"id":115,"text":"Obama told CNN en Español anchor Juan Carlos Lopez in an interview last week .","depth":10},{"id":116,"text":"This is Obama 's third nomination to the high court .","depth":10},{"id":117,"text":"Sonia Sotomayor and Elena Kagan were confirmed in 2009 and 2010 , respectively .","depth":10},{"id":118,"text":"But those confirmation hearings and votes occurred","depth":10},{"id":119,"text":"when Democrats were firmly in control of the Senate .","depth":10},{"id":120,"text":"Democrats have already begun a campaign","depth":10},{"id":121,"text":"to pressure Republicans into considering Obama 's nomination .","depth":10},{"id":122,"text":"In their sights :","depth":10},{"id":123,"text":"vulnerable senators up for reelection ,","depth":11},{"id":124,"text":"some of whom are already facing backlash from opponents","depth":12},{"id":125,"text":"for refusing to consider even a hypothetical Obama nominee .","depth":12},{"id":126,"text":"The White House launched a Twitter account , @ SCOTUSnom ,","depth":9},{"id":127,"text":"designed to promote the nomination as well .","depth":9},{"id":128,"text":"But","depth":11},{"id":129,"text":"while some moderate Republicans have expressed willingness","depth":12},{"id":130,"text":"to meet with the nominee ,","depth":12},{"id":131,"text":"their ability","depth":12},{"id":132,"text":"to force hearings before the full judiciary panel","depth":12},{"id":133,"text":"appear slim .","depth":11},{"id":134,"text":"A McConnell aide said","depth":11},{"id":135,"text":"noted the Kentucky senator voted against Garland","depth":13},{"id":136,"text":"when he was confirmed to the appeals court in 1997","depth":13},{"id":137,"text":"and argued","depth":13},{"id":138,"text":"Obama 's choice is a recognition","depth":15},{"id":139,"text":"that this pick not getting through","depth":15},{"id":140,"text":"-- otherwise the President would have picked a younger nominee","depth":15},{"id":141,"text":"who would serve longer .","depth":15},{"id":142,"text":"Sen. Pat Roberts , one of seven current Republicans","depth":14},{"id":143,"text":"to vote for Garland in 1997 ,","depth":14},{"id":144,"text":"told CNN","depth":13},{"id":145,"text":"he will not back the judge now .","depth":12},{"id":146,"text":"`` It 's not about the person .","depth":15},{"id":147,"text":"It 's about the process .","depth":15},{"id":148,"text":"Let the people decide , ''","depth":14},{"id":149,"text":"Roberts said .","depth":13},{"id":150,"text":"Asked why he voted for Garland previously ,","depth":13},{"id":151,"text":"Roberts replied ,","depth":14},{"id":152,"text":"`` I supported him . ''","depth":14},{"id":153,"text":"Trump said","depth":11},{"id":154,"text":"he agrees with the stance of the Hill Republicans .","depth":11},{"id":155,"text":"`` I think","depth":13},{"id":156,"text":"the next president should make the pick .","depth":13},{"id":157,"text":"And I think","depth":13},{"id":158,"text":"they should n't go forward .","depth":13},{"id":159,"text":"And I believe","depth":13},{"id":160,"text":"I 'm pretty much in line with what the Republicans are saying , ''","depth":13},{"id":161,"text":"Trump told CNN 's Chris Cuomo Wednesday on `` New Day .","depth":12},{"id":162,"text":"'' Toobin said","depth":11},{"id":163,"text":"it will be difficult for them to change tactics now .","depth":11},{"id":164,"text":"`` I do n't see how at this point they can go back on this promise , ''","depth":12},{"id":165,"text":"not to move on the nominee ,","depth":12},{"id":166,"text":"Toobin said Wednesday morning .","depth":11},{"id":167,"text":"Polls show","depth":9},{"id":168,"text":"most Americans support giving a nominee a congressional hearing .","depth":9},{"id":169,"text":"A CNN/ORC survey","depth":11},{"id":170,"text":"taken late last month","depth":11},{"id":171,"text":"indicated","depth":10},{"id":172,"text":"sizable majorities of Republicans , Democrats and independents want Senate Republican leaders to hold hearings on the nominee .","depth":9},{"id":173,"text":"Grassley last week said","depth":10},{"id":174,"text":"the Senate retained a prerogative","depth":11},{"id":175,"text":"to forgo hearings for Obama 's selection .","depth":11},{"id":176,"text":"`` It is n't any different","depth":12},{"id":177,"text":"if the President of the United States notifies Congress well in advance of a piece of legislation","depth":13},{"id":178,"text":"that he 's going to veto it , ''","depth":13},{"id":179,"text":"Grassley said at a Judiciary panel hearing ,","depth":11},{"id":180,"text":"citing criticism from Republicans over the role of the high court .","depth":10},{"id":181,"text":"`` Whether it 's today or tomorrow","depth":12},{"id":182,"text":"or whether it 's for the next seven or eight months ,","depth":12},{"id":183,"text":"this is a very important debate","depth":12},{"id":184,"text":"that we ought to have about the Constitution and about not only who 's going to be a replacement for Justice Scalia but about the role of the Supreme Court , ''","depth":12},{"id":185,"text":"he added .","depth":10},{"id":186,"text":"`` At the grassroots of America , there 's a real feeling","depth":11},{"id":187,"text":"of","depth":11},{"id":188,"text":"'Is the Supreme Court doing what the Constitution requires ? ' ''","depth":10},{"id":189,"text":"The announcement comes 32 days after Scalia 's death ,","depth":6},{"id":190,"text":"only slightly longer","depth":7},{"id":191,"text":"than it took him to name his two previous appointments to the high court .","depth":7},{"id":192,"text":"Unlike his nominations of Sotomayor and Kagan , the vacancy this time was n't expected .","depth":6},{"id":193,"text":"White House officials have said","depth":8},{"id":194,"text":"they were n't anticipating another Supreme Court nomination during Obama 's term ahead of Scalia 's death .","depth":8},{"id":195,"text":"Obama oversaw a team","depth":10},{"id":196,"text":"led by his counsel Neil Eggleston , chief of staff Denis McDonough , and his senior adviser Brian Deese","depth":10},{"id":197,"text":"to select and vet a group of potential nominees .","depth":9},{"id":198,"text":"After conducting interviews last week ,","depth":9},{"id":199,"text":"Obama narrowed his list","depth":10},{"id":200,"text":"to include Merrick , Watford and Srinivasan ,","depth":11},{"id":201,"text":"each of them","depth":12},{"id":202,"text":"considered `` consensus '' candidates for their history","depth":13},{"id":203,"text":"in gaining confirmation support from Republicans .","depth":13},{"id":204,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":5},{"id":205,"text":"Poll :","depth":6},{"id":206,"text":"Obama should nominate new justice","depth":6},{"id":207,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":6},{"id":208,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":8},{"id":209,"text":"Poll :","depth":9},{"id":210,"text":"Obama should nominate new justice","depth":9},{"id":211,"text":"01:28","depth":7},{"id":212,"text":"Any replacement of Scalia has the power","depth":8},{"id":213,"text":"to tilt the ideological balance of the court for decades , something","depth":9},{"id":214,"text":"conservatives are using","depth":10},{"id":215,"text":"to move their base","depth":11},{"id":216,"text":"to hold the line .","depth":11},{"id":217,"text":"`` This seat could be transformational to the court","depth":11},{"id":218,"text":"because Justice Scalia 's fidelity to the Constitution was a real anchor for the court .","depth":11},{"id":219,"text":"If he were replaced by an Obama nominee","depth":11},{"id":220,"text":"that would give the court a solid five votes","depth":12},{"id":221,"text":"for enacting an extremely liberal agenda","depth":13},{"id":222,"text":"that the American people will not be comfortable with , ''","depth":13},{"id":223,"text":"Carrie Severino , of Judicial Crisis Network , a conservative group opposed to any candidate","depth":11},{"id":224,"text":"getting a hearing until after the election .","depth":11},{"id":225,"text":"It would shift the court","depth":12},{"id":226,"text":"-- that is somewhat balanced --","depth":12},{"id":227,"text":"to a liberal stronghold .","depth":11},{"id":228,"text":"She is a former clerk of Justice Clarence Thomas .","depth":8},{"id":229,"text":"Since Scalia 's death and for the foreseeable future , the court has operated with eight justices , four","depth":10},{"id":230,"text":"appointed by Democrats","depth":10},{"id":231,"text":"and four by Republicans .","depth":9},{"id":232,"text":"Justices have been considering several major cases ,","depth":9},{"id":233,"text":"including a challenge to public sector unions , a race-conscious admissions plan at the University of Texas , the first big abortion case since 2007 , challenges to voting rights , the Affordable Care Act 's contraceptive mandate and a challenge to Obama 's executive actions on immigration .","depth":9},{"id":234,"text":"Scalia 's death means not only the loss of the court 's main conservative voice","depth":9},{"id":235,"text":"but also increases the likelihood of a 4-4 split on controversial issues .","depth":9},{"id":236,"text":"If the court is equally divided in a case ,","depth":10},{"id":237,"text":"ruling 4-4 ,","depth":10},{"id":238,"text":"it means the lower court opinion stands","depth":10},{"id":239,"text":"and there is no precedent","depth":11},{"id":240,"text":"set by the Supreme Court .","depth":11}],"relations":[{"parent":481,"left":0,"right":480,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":480,"left":343,"right":479,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":343,"left":258,"right":342,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":258,"left":246,"right":257,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":246,"left":243,"right":245,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":243,"left":242,"right":3,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":242,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":245,"left":4,"right":244,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":244,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":257,"left":254,"right":256,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":254,"left":250,"right":253,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":250,"left":248,"right":249,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":248,"left":7,"right":247,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":247,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":249,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":253,"left":12,"right":252,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":252,"left":13,"right":251,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":251,"left":14,"right":15,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":256,"left":16,"right":255,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":255,"left":17,"right":18,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":342,"left":277,"right":341,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":277,"left":272,"right":276,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":272,"left":268,"right":271,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":268,"left":263,"right":267,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":263,"left":19,"right":262,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":262,"left":20,"right":261,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":261,"left":21,"right":260,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":260,"left":259,"right":24,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":259,"left":22,"right":23,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":267,"left":266,"right":29,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":266,"left":265,"right":28,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":265,"left":25,"right":264,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":264,"left":26,"right":27,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":271,"left":30,"right":270,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":270,"left":31,"right":269,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":269,"left":32,"right":33,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":276,"left":34,"right":275,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":275,"left":274,"right":38,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":274,"left":35,"right":273,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":273,"left":36,"right":37,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":341,"left":298,"right":340,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":298,"left":282,"right":297,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":282,"left":278,"right":281,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":278,"left":39,"right":40,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":281,"left":41,"right":280,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":280,"left":279,"right":44,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":279,"left":42,"right":43,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":297,"left":283,"right":296,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":283,"left":45,"right":46,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":296,"left":286,"right":295,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":286,"left":285,"right":50,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":285,"left":284,"right":49,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":284,"left":47,"right":48,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":295,"left":51,"right":294,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":294,"left":290,"right":293,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":290,"left":289,"right":56,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":289,"left":287,"right":288,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":287,"left":52,"right":53,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":288,"left":54,"right":55,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":293,"left":292,"right":60,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":292,"left":57,"right":291,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":291,"left":58,"right":59,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":340,"left":307,"right":339,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":307,"left":300,"right":306,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":300,"left":61,"right":299,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":299,"left":62,"right":63,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":306,"left":303,"right":305,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":303,"left":64,"right":302,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":302,"left":301,"right":67,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent"